We have NEVER missed a payment. I have great credit history and income to qualify for any of the Bella Vista units. After I spoke to Chaqya face to face at Bella Vista to apply for the apartment, she told me that it was after 5:00 pm and my parents should go there the next morning for the process of applying. I told her that I have to be their guarantor and she said it is fine as long as we qualify. I asked her what of someone apply before us until the next morning and she assured me that won't happen. The next day my parents went there to get the application started and she told them that I have to apply online. Since I was at work I called her to get the online information and she told me that the apartment has another applicant. I was surprised and said that she assured me the night before that won't happen after my complaint she said let me call you back maybe they don't qualify. She called me back 10 minutes later saying the other applicants didn't qualify and we are good to go. She emailed me links to online application and told me to add everyone who will live in the unit plus myself as a guarantor on the application. I did and emailed her the confirmation. I also paid $188 for all of our credit checks plus $600 deposit. She emailed back saying it all seems good and asked for my paystubs, copy of DL, and my employer information. Plus she wanted to verify my mom's SS card in person. So she asked me to go with my mom to the office and since she was going to be out of the office for couple of days said that anyone in the office can verify that. So I took my mom on the same day and showed up at their office where I was told by another agent Jovani that they do not allow guarantor for more than one person and that one individual has to be a college student. My parents are clearly not college students and more than one person. Clearly I was surprised and he suggested to cancel the application and I said as long as I will get my money back. If I knew that they do not allow guarantor for anyone other than one student WHY would I apply????

It is over a month later and after several visits, emails, and phone calls with that office I have received the $600 back but not the $188 credit check. I am in the process of filing to sue them in small claim court. Every time I went to their office there were several people complaining about different things and their agents were like robots with no real care for their tenants and clients. Also this policy of not accepting guarantor is not mentioned ANYWHERE!!! Not brought up by their agents and not on their application. Their online program allows to add more than one person who are not students in addition to a guarantor. I have been a tenant, landlord, and home owner and I have never been treated poorly by an organization. Charging $2300 for a 1 bed 1 bath apartments, you would think at least they treat you fairly. I strongly recommend that you look elsewhere if you are thinking about living there. There are many beautiful buildings in that neighborhood with way better management. < text>
8/9/2015

I cant wait till my lease is up!

Gated community my arse! the left wing gates are always broken and open (4 months now), even seen the gates hit nice Mercedez and just destroy the paint on them (Bella Vista of course has no security cams on gates, so they are not responsible for damages).
Security Guards are a joke!!!!, they walk around smelling daisies and harassing with unwanted conversation to the point that I have to be rude and tell them to shut up and stop talking. They avoid big, crowded scenes (especially when they are rowdy)- isn't this what they are supposed to take care of, lol.

Subsidized living!- More and more I have noticed this place take in people with "ghetto" backgrounds. They are loud, disrespectful, have no boundary respects and think they still live in Pacoima/Downtown.

*My 19 year old sister had a black MAN MID-30'S harass her until she gave him a fake number about a house party that was going on, poolside, no security present (main children's pool btw). I thought they checked for this type of behavior. Now I feel like I need to present with her at all times when she is enjoying the pool.

*Another event- we had a incident happen where another disorderly man was LITERALLY TRYING TO KICK OUR DOWN DOWN, called security, nothing happened then called the cops to take care of the situation, I HAD TO STEP OUT, AND CONFRONT THIS RANDOM MAN MYSELF TO TELL HIM TO LEAVE AS THE COPS WERE ON THEIR WAY AND I SAW 2!!! TWO!! 1+1=2!!! SECURITY GUARDS SITTING IN THEIR ELECTRIC CART. chilling.

HOWEVER!- cleaning crew, and room maintenance people are always on spot. Yes, it is a large place so keeping up can get hard when dogs are marking every wall. But I do get up at odd hours of the crack of dawn and I see the cleaning crews busting their ass, So Bella Vista is doing that right.

I wouldnt be surprised if my tires get punctured/vandalized after I post this. 8/9/2015
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

So, I am about to move in. Reading all the reviews a bit late, I feel they are "baiting and snatching" me. We were promised one unit, 7 days before our move in date, they tell us we cant move in (after reservation, holding deposits and a month ahead of moving date.) Then they try giving me a horrible view, worn down apt that fits my moving date, as a nicety, telling me its a much more expensive unit ( i guess vintage?, lol). So, i bite the bullet and opt for a larger unit, more expense, and i cant even see it, but "it will be available to move in within 2 days". Lets see what happens now. Ill probably make a specific blog for this place alone.

i have to say, staff is nice, the place looks clean, and quiet. Ill update within my 30 day guarantee, thats if they dont decide to keep my deposit and bring me ridiculous charges as i have been reading.

<Time>1602128454678</Time><Rate>5< /Rate>< review>
Hello, potential contractors this is a student of CSLS recently, I have been in the trades for over 15yrs and going to make the move to become a contractor this decision doesn't come lightly i could have just fill my application , take the test with the state but wait this isn't something you should do without knowledge. One bright and educated individual by the name Pegi Burdick helped me make a decision on becoming a smarter tradesman on business and law of the trade which will help me navigate through the paper work jobs will demand.  The information, CDs, packet of study guides and well put binder will help me succeed all I have to do is apply myself and if I need any questions answered  Pegi Burdick does a  wonderful job getting that information and point you in the next step of the process. I do recommend this school before you do it yourself you don't want to go blind into this business of trades.<//review>

< Text>
I want to say thank you to everyone at CSLS especially Alyssa Ramirez.She was there from the first day I walked into the Van Nuys location to filling out the final paperwork to submit to the CSLB after passing both exams (on the first try). She was always available to answer any questions I had and  advise me of what I needed every step of the way. Alyssa, Thank you again!!
All the instructors were very knowledgeable and presented the information in an easy to understand format that was very similar to the format of the state exams.
All the study material was spot on. Very well organized and a great balance of text and audio. All the tests in the books were great study material in the 3 or 4 days prior to taking the exams.
I completed and passed the law section of the exam in just under an hour and the General B exam in just over an hour and a half. If it wasn't for CSLS, their amazing staff, and the way the study material is laid out I don't think I would have been able to breeze thru both exams the way that I did.

Thank you again to everyone at CSLS
Craig Toeller< /Text>

brad gardiner< /name>
<time>1590202885650</time>< Rate>
5</Rate>
< Text>
This is a family shop that makes everything from scratch!

Emerson and his wife (owners) are the kindest people you will likely ever meet.

We bought a house a few blocks from the taqueria a few months ago (11/2019).  They got us thru the hassle of the move by making our lunch and dinners - I don't know how many times.

Been back again and again.  Not a single mistake on any item we highly customized (we are picky).

Emerson told me they just opened around the same time we moved here.  He loves to talk and you will find he has a story for everything.  His wife (only there on a couple of our visits  - got caught up talking and forgot to get her name) is just as friendly.

Food:  Off the hook.

Price: Same

Recommendation: Get anything they have that has refried beans, if you like those.  They are, well...find out for yourself.

Conclusion: Taco Bell is like a block or 2 away.  Forget that!</Text>

We had friends saying the place was great, saw the long lines in many occasions and got tricked into trying. The lines are mostly due to inefficient service, with employees trying to do multiple things at the same time. The girls were crossing in front of each other and one ice cream almost ended up on the floor. At one point each one of 3 groups of customers had 1 ice cream each and were waiting for the rest of their orders, and none of the employees was mixing ice cream (not sure where they all went? Seemed like they were not organized at all). That cold stone where the ice cream is mixed with other stuff does not look like the most hygienic thing. <Rate>4</Rate>< Text>
This place is a very nice place to go with friends to have a classic ice cream cone/ cup (or ever alone!) They have a nice assortment of flavors, nothing out of the ordinary. The ice cream was delicious and you can add your own toppings as such, although the employee seemed irritated if we asked a question such as "Does the ice cream have egg?" Overall, good experience.< /Text>

<Review>My kids would give it a five star rating.  My 16 year-old daughter loves the 'cake batter' ice cream, and my youngest loves just going out for ice cream PERIOD.  She informed me that all ice cream is good - Baskin Robbins, ColdStone, anything.  As for myself, I find the ice cream too sweet, the store overwhelmingly smelly in a sweet sort of way, and the ice cream texture like Gelato.

The staff is very friendly and helpful and will SING if you give them a tip - so definitely tip.  It's very funny.

Lines can be very long - even on a good day, and move slowly.  But among the best ice cream in Fremont, if you like a sweet gelato style.< /Review>< pictures>

It seems I can always find what I am looking for with Eddy Bauer. Their outlet store at Vintage Oaks Shopping Center is my goto place for clothing. Maybe because I like Eddie Bauer as a brand but also the quality is excellent and the selection at this store is always good. I am an average size guy and outlet/discount stores seem to lack the sizes of the average person. I think you know. Racks with small and extra large are always available, but try to find your size if you are in the normal range. Try Eddie Bauer. I am not an employee, just a good customer.<//review>

101928212714585492266<//userid>
<review>Great taproom with some tasty IPA‚Äôs, friendly staff, and comfortable atmosphere. Noel, the taproom manager, is the shizzle!<//review><gmapID>0x80850caeb8cc1267:0x42094175dad05e37< /gmapID><response>None< /response><time>1506729798011< /time></record>
</dataset><record>
< rate>
4</rate>
< resp>
None<//resp>
< Review>
I always stop here on my way to Sonoma. It is a great location and a great atmosphere. The beer is good. They have a wide range of choices and styles that will appease any beer lover and causal drinker alike. If you are a beer enthusiast, or have a developed palate, you WILL pick up on the various nuances in their styles. It is nice, for instance they have a fairly constant, ever-changing rotation of brews on tap. They may have a couple, or three brown ales, for example. You can try them and pick out the subtle differences in them. Much like how wineries will have three different varietals cabernet sauvignon to taste.  Now, for some of the reviewers on here, this may be too much for them handle, which is fine, but then I would suggest getting a more "diverse selection" of styles, a selection where you can tell yourself "yes, now I know that is a stout, or yes, I know that is an IPA, I am sooooo good at beering!" You know, to make you feel better about yourself. I have thoroughly enjoyed all of their IPA's and pale ales. If you find that their IPA's do not fit the name they have chosen or are not bitter enough for you, all you simply have to do is ingest your outlook on life and reviews of breweries on Google to supplement your perceived "lack-of hoppiness/bitterness. Anyways, I have always had a great experience here. Friendly staff (not snobby at all), very casual atmosphere, and the beer is good. I always stop to get a growler fill and see what new beers they have on tap. If you are in the area, check it out and do not pass on this place. Don't listen to the naysayer. In fact, never listen to them. I always understand that their beer may not be a hit for everyone, no place ever is, just always be weary about a review that can't find one good selection out of the many that are offered. Check them out for yourself and form your own opinion. You won't be disappointed. Oh and the shuffleboard costs like 50 cents to play... so be sure to bring the family gold...< /Review>

< Text>
So my opinion my be biased because I am a bit of a book work, but I really like this location. The staff have always been super helpful and the place is always neat and tidy. My family and I visited to pick up some new books and take advantage of the sweet 50% off deals they had going on. At check out everything went smoothly, we paid for our stuff and just as we were about to leave the store associate that rang us up said, "wait, I'm sorry, but may I take a look at your receipt?" So, we handed it to him and just as he suspected one of the deals (buy 3 books get free tote) didn't ring up correctly and we had been charged for the tote. He made sure to check that all of the other deals went through and refunded the price of the tote. The entire time he had an amazing attitude and seem to genuinely care about the customers. He even kept thanking us for waiting while he corrected the systems mistake. We of course expressed how thankful we were because we probably wouldn't of noticed until we got home. This Barnes & Noble is a favorite in our book üòâ</Text>

<UserId.>105474155968239481697< /UserId.>< name>
Yellowstone< /name>
< Time>
1575756083631<//Time>
<rating>3</rating>< review>
We were there with our two grandchildren to shop and attend the storytime. Unknown to us the first Saturday of the month is a service dog event.
It was very difficult to find room to enjoy the story due to the fact there were 10 to 12 large dogs situated up next to the stage listening area. The children had to take a back seat to the dogs.
Due to the lack of room and the inability to see or hear the story many of the families left, it was not a pleasant experience.
Suggestion: have the dogs at the other end of the children's section with the table and covered area. This will leave room to enjoy the children's storytime.
We also left without making the purchases we wanted too. Guess we will use Amazon too bad for the bottom line of one of the last existing bookstores.< /review>

<Time>1514424005249< /Time>< gmapID>
0x80c328b1ab56c961:0xf8ab7f84acaaca9d</gmapID>
< text>
The store is always well stocked and maintained (minus the collectibles area but that is where the children roam.) There is an extensive ground floor open area that can be explored with ease, and help is always within earshot range. The help counter, which is located at the heart of the store, always has an associate that is willing to go the full 100 yards to assist you in finding what you are looking for, or to simply give you a recommendation. If you are looking for a friendly, yet clam and semi-quiet, place to purchase a book then this would be a good choice.

There is never really a large line in the check-out lanes, but if there is, you may have to wait a few minutes (they usually only ever have 1-2 cashiers working at one time) but the line is handled well.<//text>

<user>107025041939728076657< /user><Pictures>None<//Pictures><review>I visited this particular : Barnes And Noble store , on : Thursday , February 5th 2015 . The customer service is excellent. The shopping center surroundings are simply magnificent . AMC Theatre just a little north of this splendid and magnificent book store. Then the gym I so love: 24 Hour Fitness Gym. By eating properly and good work outs have lost ten pounds . My cholesterol levels have amazingly improved . So its wonderful after a good movie and an excellent work to venture to : Barnes And Noble , relax on very nice relaxing seat with soft music playing in the back ground .Then have my favorite latte or just a very nice coffee at : The Star Buck's in the book store. I was some what dismayed the Barnes And Nobel in West Covina is no longer there . Yet this one is so easy to get to its so easy to find. From: Azusa south ,right on Gladstone and left on : Shellman Ave. Its a very nice shopping center it does have nice posted signs to prevent trouble makers and some cameras . I love this additional safety. Especially if I go shopping and have leave a few items in my car. They hopefully will be apprehended . My experience was wonderful at this : Barnes And Nobel. I wanted to obtain a certain book the very nice and professional customer service is beyond words. Exemplary  , outstanding performance of the very beautiful blond and beautiful Latina ,to me beyond the call of duty. At both occasions as both were very busy actually stopped what they were in the process of doing to show concern with customer service love to order me a book not yet available in the store . This is how I love being treated . Along with the sir or Ms.  Supposedly some stores have closed because some customers choose to shop online. The significant problem with shopping online is the obvious: Identity theft. It is not solved and will always be a problem . I myself love to pay in cash. So if the excuse is to save money . Then ask any victim of identity theft how much did it cost to fix their credit rating ? Was it worth it gambling like this ? Plus all the pain and suffering just to save only a few dollars . When they could have enjoyed a very nice Latte or very nice : Starbuck's coffee . Relax after a great movie and a good relaxing work out , at :24 Hour Fitness. Then complete my journey with a very nice book to glance at , while relaxing to soft music in the back ground. This it self is such excellent therapy . Who ever invented : Barnes And Nobel should be put in for a award. As far as these two wonderful employees . Their display of kindness , patience love and under standing with exemplary customer service performance . They should properly be awarded. A  Certificate Of Excellence Award , in front of the store from the corporate office. On perhaps customer service recognition day. Just relaxing in a very nice customer friendly environment helps my chronic back arthritis temporarily go away. I do pray more stores do reopen. God Bless. I do hope if its not too much to ask : If the local Christian community can join me in harmonious prayer that more stores like this open . So much to offer . I felt the love, the care . It so helped me temporarily for a moment think of my recent pet that recently past on , in new light. In stead of being in mourning . Here I found a type of : Refuge . After a great movie a great work out. Some where to relax to soothing music with a coffee and a latte and glance at a nice relaxing book. With : Exemplary customer service. What else could we want . Not to exaggerate , but to some extent : It was like perhaps : Heaven on earth. Please keep up the excellent customer service: Barnes And Nobel. God Bless.<//review>< Gmap_id>
